# EverythingFlow Industry Page Skill

This skill builds a complete, standalone HTML industry-landing page for **Everything Flow** (the B2B web-development sister) or **Everything Design** (the B2B brand parent), mirroring the canonical patterns established for:

- `https://everythingflow.agency/solution/energy-web-development-design-agency`
- `https://everythingflow.agency/solution/cybersecurity-web-development-design-agency`
- `https://everythingflow.agency/solution/deeptech-web-development-design-agency`

And optionally a companion long-form blog post for the parent site at everything.design, modelled on the deeptech essay *"Not a Technology Problem. A Design Problem."*

## When to use

Trigger this skill whenever the user asks for:

- An industry, vertical, or sub-sector landing page for Everything Flow or Everything Design
- A long-form thought-leadership blog tied to one of those pages
- *"Build me a [fintech / cybersecurity / healthcare / climate / aerospace / robotics / biotech / semiconductor / spacetech / deeptech] page"*
- *"Like the cyber page but for [X]"*
- *"Make a [industry] industry page for everythingflow"*

If the user names an industry without specifying the destination, **ask which of these two routes they want before starting:**

- **everythingflow.agency** = B2B **web-development** sister. Positioning is web development first; Webflow is the build stack, not the identifier. H2s end "...at/by Everything Flow." Title pattern: *"[Industry] Web Development Agency | B2B Web Development & Design for [Industry] | Everything Flow"*.
- **everything.design** = B2B **brand and design** parent. Positioning is brand strategy, brand identity, naming, B2B branding. H2s end "...at Everything Design." Use everything.design canonical ranking terms (`b2b branding agency`, `b2b web design agency`, `b2b website design agency`, `3d websites`).

The blog (the everything.design thought-leadership essay) always anchors on everything.design and links the deep deeptech/cyber/energy page on everythingflow.agency as further reading. Routing the CTA matters: an everything.design blog ends with `everything.design/contact-us`; an everythingflow.agency page ends with `everythingflow.agency/contact`.

