### "Why us — engineers building for engineers" section

This is the differentiator block, especially powerful for deeptech and other engineering-heavy verticals. Structure:

- H2 (AEO): *"Why is Everything Flow different from other [industry] web development agencies?"*
- Left narrative panel: founder POV paragraphs. Include — years on [industry]; firsthand learning; **VC trust line** ("That's why VCs like Stellaris and impact-deeptech partners like Social Alpha trust us with their portfolio companies"); the team composition line ("Strategy, copy, design, development, 3D, 2D — all under one roof"); the "best technology in the world shouldn't be stopped by a lack of translation" thesis.
- Right side: accent-bordered POV box with the canonical line *"The most consequential companies in [X] are losing to companies with weaker technology — simply because the world cannot understand what they have built. This is not a technology problem. It's a design problem."*
- 4-cell stats grid below. Tiles to choose from: Years on [industry] (6 yrs); VCs that trust us (Stellaris, Social Alpha); Sectors we know (industry-specific list); Trained in (Design sustainability + comms design + mechanical engineering).
- Engineer-grid: 4 cards = Mejo Kuriachan (Founder, Mechanical Engineer) · Vignesh (3D Lead, Mechanical Engineer) · Akshay A D (Project Manager, Mechanical Engineer) · Saurabh Chakradhari (Web Dev Lead, Aerospace Engineer). Plus a wide combo card below for Sijeesh (Lead Strategist) + Ekta + Zakia + Tanmaya (engineering-fluent designers).
- Closing line: *"The combination is the point. Mechanical engineers in founder, 3D and PM roles + an aerospace engineer leading web dev — paired with a strategist and senior designers who've extensively worked with engineers."*

### Field note POV — canonical quote

For deeptech: *"The most consequential companies in deep tech are losing to companies with weaker technology — simply because the world cannot understand what they have built. This is not a technology problem. It's a design problem. That's the gap we exist to close."* — Mejo Kuriachan & Ekta Manchanda.

For cybersecurity: *"If a brand is the impression you leave on a customer, branding is impression management. In cybersecurity, you're selling something invisible — and the legacy players are still winning on brand equity..."* — Swathi Mohan & Sanjana.

For new verticals, derive an equivalent thesis. The tension is always *capability vs. translation* — the company is strong on capability and weak on translation.

### Featured/marquee case study card

Set `class="case featured"`. CSS makes it `grid-column:1 / -1` and turns it into a two-column layout (frame left, body right). Marquee badge in the live bar, "★ Featured" in the industry tag, marquee pills row with 6 tech-stack chips, longer body copy (2 paragraphs), 4-cell "by the numbers" instead of 3.

Use this for the most visually dramatic / high-volume client (Armory for deeptech; SISA for cybersecurity).

