### Companion blog (everything.design)

For high-value industry pages, write a long-form 2000–2500 word essay for the everything.design blog. Pattern (modelled on *"Not a Technology Problem. A Design Problem."*):

- **Title**: *"[Provocative thesis statement]"* — short, declarative, opinionated.
- **Dek**: subtitle explaining the thesis.
- **Byline**: *"By Mejo Kuriachan & Ekta Manchanda · Founders, Everything Design · A B2B branding and design agency for [industry] · X min read"*.
- **Section structure**: 1) Opening hook with the thesis. 2) The gap most studios have. 3) The cost of bad translation (compounds in fundraising, sales, talent). 4) Why we built it differently (founder origin, years on the discipline, VC trust). 5) The team composition (4 engineers in 4 roles + strategy/design engineering-fluent partners). 6) What it looks like in practice (every real client gets a paragraph). 7) What changes when you get it right. 8) Closing thesis + CTA.
- **CTA link**: route through `everything.design/contact-us` (NOT everythingflow.agency).
- **Further reading**: link the matching everythingflow.agency industry page + every client case study on everything.design + adjacent sister-vertical pages.
- **Bio footer**: explicit *"Everything Design is a B2B branding and design agency... The Webflow build is delivered through our sister studio, Everything Flow."* — routes the web execution to the sister brand.
- **Brand/design keyword density**: weave in *B2B branding agency*, *design agency*, *brand strategy*, *brand identity*, *B2B branding* (these are everything.design's strongest ranking terms).

### Footer

Five columns: brand blurb / Projects / Solutions / Industries / Contact. The Solutions list is where you encode the high-traffic anchor terms specific to the destination:

- **Everything Flow Solutions**: *Deeptech Web Development Agency · B2B Web Development for [Industry] · Web Development Agency for Hardware Startups · 3D Website Agency · GSAP Scroll Animation Development · CMS Migration · Premium Webflow Partner Build*.
- **Everything Design Solutions**: *B2B Branding Agency for [Industry] · B2B Web Design Agency · Brand Strategy for [Industry] · Brand Identity & Naming · 3D Brand Renders*.

Always end with "Bengaluru, India" and update the "Last Updated" date to today.

## SEO + AEO + entity coverage check

After writing the file, run two coverage passes:

```bash
# Coverage of primary keywords (commercial intent)
for k in "[primary]" "[secondary]" ... ; do
  c=$(grep -ci "$k" /path/to/page.html); echo "$c × $k";
done

# Coverage of named entities (case studies + investors + people)
for e in "[Client1]" "[Client2]" "[Investor]" "[Founder name]" ... ; do
  c=$(grep -c "$e" /path/to/page.html); echo "$c × $e";
done
```

Each primary keyword: at least 2× (title + H1 + body). Each named entity: at least 2× (case study + AEO FAQ section). The AEO FAQ section is the strongest place for entity reinforcement.

